[]: TV deaths of Misato and Rits - your initial reactions? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by Maya Ibuki &raquo; Thu Sep 17, 2015 1:22 pm Though their deaths were explicitly shown in EoE, I was wondering what people initially thought of the glimpses provided in TV? Anyone a fan around that time care to comment? This, of course, only applies to those who watched TV before the feature films. It is ambiguous -- shots of Misato and Ritsuko dead on the floor - but we are never shown on TV as to who shot them. Do you think Anno at this stage thought that far ahead? Or were they just included to show the despair Shinji is describing - and not necessarily meant to be focused on per say? It explains the short glimpses. They are also left to interpretation as per Kaji&#39;s. Furthermore, do you think Anno came up with their EoE deaths as a way to shut fans up? Were how they died in EoE implied in EoTV? Was it his plan all along? There&#39;s no way whatsoever that I would&#39;ve come to the conclusion that Ritsuko had been shot by Gendo without watching EoE... so just curious as to people&#39;s initial reactions.

